{"lemma":"أَسِيرٌ","slug":"أَسِيرٌ","root":"#.س.ر","root_slug":"_-س-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/_-س-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَسِير","root":"أسر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n752",""],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"prisoner of war, captive","examples":[{"text":"يفرج عن أسرى الحرب ويعادون إلى أوطانهم دون إبطاء بعد انتهاء الأعمال العدائية الفعلية.","english":"Prisoners of war shall be released and repatriated without delay after the cessation of active hostilities."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"* Diachronically inherited from Proto-Semitic *ʔasīr-.\n* Synchronically belonging to the root ء س ر (ʔ s r) meaning “to fetter” in the base stem.\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/ʔa.siːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n752","headword_ar":"اَسِيرٌ","root":"Asr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^osuwrN","text_ar":"مَاْسُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bound with an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isaAr","text_ar":"اـِسَار"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shackled:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imprisoned:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mujáhid, M, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"captived,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a captive;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"absolutely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"although not bound with an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsAr","text_ar":"اسار"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isaArN","text_ar":"اـِسَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes used in the same sense. (Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asyr","text_ar":"اسير"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied as an epithet to a woman, (Mgh, Msb,) when the woman is mentioned; but otherwise"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asiyrapN","text_ar":"اَسِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as the fem.: you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qatalotu AlA^asiyrapa","text_ar":"قَتَلْتُ الاَسِيرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I slew the female captive"},{"kind":"text","text":"], like as you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu Alqatiylapa","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ القَتِيلَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) The pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoraY","text_ar":"اَسْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaraA='u","text_ar":"اَسَرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and (accord. to several authors, pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoraY","text_ar":"اَسْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usaAraY","text_ar":"اُسَارَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAraY","text_ar":"اَسَارَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) the first of these forms of pl. is proper to epithets applied to those who are hurt or afflicted in their bodies or their intellects: (Aboo-Is-hák:) it is used in this instance because a captive is like one wounded or stung. (Th, M.)"}],"source_refs":["M","TA","K","S","Mgh","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}